In Scheme you can implement the following FROM SCRATCH, in PURE
SCHEME CODE:

- Object orientation
  - Meta-object protocol
- Exception handling
  - Upward exceptions (try-catch)
  - Restartable exceptions (try-catch-restart)
- Concurrency
  - Light-weight threads (aka green threads)
  - Channels

... "In lisp, the easy is difficult, but the impossible is possible"
- who said this?
